    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 6 @ 2022/2023",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A magnet has two poles, it is therefore called a magnetic",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "dipole",
        "monopole",
        "pole",
        "field"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "dipole"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;'><h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>Magnetic Poles</h3><p>Every magnet has two poles:</p><ul><li><strong>North pole</strong> (seeks Earth's magnetic south)</li><li><strong>South pole</strong> (seeks Earth's magnetic north)</li></ul><h4 style='color: #2c3e50; margin-top: 15px;'>Terminology:</h4><ul><li><strong>Dipole</strong>: A system with two poles (correct term for magnets).</li><li><strong>Monopole</strong>: A hypothetical single pole (not observed in nature).</li><li><strong>Pole</strong>: Refers to one end, not the entire magnet.</li><li><strong>Field</strong>: The region where magnetic forces act.</li></ul><p>Thus, a magnet is a <strong>magnetic dipole</strong>.</p></div>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Magnetism",
      "Magnetic Fields"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 27 @ 2016/2017",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Which expression gives the maximum force on a charged particle moving in a magnetic field?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "ILV",
        "ILB",
        "IL",
        "None"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "None (Correct: \\(F = qvB\\) for perpendicular motion)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<b>Magnetic force</b> on a moving charge is:<br><br>\\(F = qvB \\sin(\\theta)\\)<br>• Maximum when \\(\\theta = 90°\\) (\\(\\sin(90°) = 1\\)).<br>• Thus, \\(F_{\\text{max}} = qvB\\).<br><br>None of the options match this. The question may be incomplete."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electromagnetism and Electrodynamics",
      "Magnetism"
    ]
  },
