  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 29 @ 2016/2017",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Biot-Savart’s law is given as:",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "\\(dB = \\frac{\\mu_0 I dl \\sin(\\theta)}{4\\pi r^2}\\)",
        "\\(dB = \\frac{\\mu_0 I dl \\sin(\\theta)}{r^2}\\)",
        "\\(dB = \\frac{I dl \\sin(\\theta)}{4\\pi r^2}\\)",
        "\\(dB = \\mu_0 I dl \\sin(\\theta)\\)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\(dB = \\frac{\\mu_0 I dl \\sin(\\theta)}{4\\pi r^2}\\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<b>Biot-Savart Law</b> describes the magnetic field (\\(dB\\)) due to a small current element (\\(I dl\\)):<br><br>\\(dB = \\frac{\\mu_0}{4\\pi} \\frac{I dl \\sin(\\theta)}{r^2}\\)<br>• \\(\\mu_0\\): Permeability of free space<br>• \\(\\theta\\): Angle between \\(dl\\) and \\(r\\)<br><br>Option (a) matches the correct formula."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electromagnetism and Electrodynamics",
      "Magnetism",
      "Current Density"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 30 @ 2016/2017",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The magnetic field of a current-carrying circular loop is expressed as:",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "B = μ₀IN/r²",
        "dB = μ₀N/4r",
        "dB = μ₀IN/4πr²",
        "dB = μ₀IN/2r"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "dB = μ₀IN/2r"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<b>Biot-Savart Law Application:</b><br>The magnetic field <b>at the center</b> of a circular loop with <i>N</i> turns, radius <i>r</i>, and current <i>I</i> is derived from:<br><br>\\( B = \\frac{\\mu_0 I N}{2r} \\)<br><br><b>Key Points:</b><br>1. <b>μ₀</b>: Permeability of free space (4π × 10⁻⁷ Tm/A)<br>2. <b>N</b>: Number of turns enhances the field proportionally<br>3. <b>2r</b>: Inverse dependence on loop radius<br><br><b>Why Other Options Fail:</b><br>- (a) Incorrect denominator (r² instead of 2r)<br>- (b) Missing current <i>I</i><br>- (c) Incorrect π term and denominator"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electromagnetism and Electrodynamics",
      "Magnetism",
      "Magnetic Fields"
    ]
  }
